reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absorbent, comfortable, convenient and greener than the conventional choices.
reviews.reviewText: I really wanted to do cloth diapers, but, unlike with my firstborn, I couldn't get them not to leak & my daughter would get instant diaper rash despite changing them immediately and most of the pee escaping. Enter, Babyganics. I did not realize they have SAP gel, or what that was; I thought it was pure plant matter inside. The bamboo based diapers are supposed to be a much greener choice, but my girl is almost potty trained, so I am sticking with these til then. She is a reverse cycling cosleeping breastfeeding baby & drinks milk every 1-2 hours overnight; these diapers keep her dry, no leaking (maybe we should send some to the White House)! Best of all, no diaper rash for my sensitive girl.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Recommend this diaper over even leading companies like honest/huggies/pampers here’s why
reviews.reviewText: We have used Babyganics for the past almost 3 years now. With two babies in diapers, working within a budget but wanting to be careful what I put on my babies sensitive skin I have found that the only diaper that works for us is Babyganics.We tried many other products to find the right fit, pampers, parents choice, huggies, honest company, and a few dye free organic options but we found all of these brands ( with the exception of Honest Company ) just didn’t hold up over time and would feel damp on the outside of the diaper soon after a pee pee happened, which to me grossed me out as a mom... just thinking about my kids in a wet diaper and then that wet diaper making their clothes damp as well. For me diapers should retain and contain moisture and the only two diapers I found to do this incredibly well were honest company and Babyganics. In store the prices seem comparable however where honest falls out is the amount of diapers you get in a box as compared to Babyganics. So for the best price and best quality the best choice for you would be Babyganics. Very happy with their diapers and recommend to all!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 31, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love these diapers
reviews.reviewText: This is the only brand of disposables we have used in my daughters 5 years of life. She is pretty tiny so she still fits in size 5 at nights. They rarely leak. I am thankful for a diaper that does not use chemicals in it. We used cloth until my daughter had rashes that would not go away. Her rashes are gone now! We will continue to use these until my daughter is completely potty trained.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars They are easy to dispose of and very little odor escapes
reviews.reviewText: I really appreciate these nappies. They very rarely leak on my two boys, unless the hose is pointed north, but that's more of a mummy error than the function of these. My youngest is 5 months and has yet to get a diaper rash. They are easy to dispose of and very little odor escapes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2021
reviews.reviewText: So soft and great for the skin. They do not hold up well overnight though so wont use them again. Baby waking up wet isnt acceptable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 2, 2022
reviews.reviewText: We have been using this brand for a year without a problem, but we just went up in size on the diaper and the batch that we received, almost every time my baby wears them they bust open on the side and the gel that is inside falls out and gets all over her skin and inside the onsie. I dont know if we received a bad/ defective batch, or is this what is to be expected from this brand when you go up in diaper size. I dont know if I want purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Be careful if your baby pulls at his diapers
reviews.reviewText: I like the diapers, but the material on the cuff around the leg can be pulled off. My son has discovered this and I am concerned he will try and eat it since he is only 11 months old.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the money
reviews.reviewText: My first son has super sensitive skin and these diapers are a lifesaver! Loved them so much I ended up buying again for my second as well even though he is not sensitive. They are super absorbent and so soft. The price point isn’t great, but the quality outweighs it.
